dc_title_s: Carte geologique detaillee de la France [a 1/80 000]: Lauterbourg
dc_description_s: France. Service de la carte geologique de France Explanatory text: 1 sheet in MC folder. North Decimal Degree 49.0074 South Decimal Degree 48.6485 East Decimal Degree 8.4662 West Decimal Degree 8.0297 Relief shown by hachures. Principal meridian: Paris. Longitude is given in centesimal values (100 grades = 90 degrees) .The Service de la carte geologique de la France was integrated to the BRGM to become the only France Service geologique national. Based on "Carte topograqphique de l'etat major."
